message: "If you use AIF in your research or workflows, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "AIF: AI-native Interchange Format and SkillForge Toolkit"
authors:
  - family-names: Chen
    given-names: Liqun
url: "https://github.com/LiqunChen0606/skillforge"
repository-code: "https://github.com/LiqunChen0606/skillforge"
license: Apache-2.0
version: 0.1.0
date-released: "2026-04-02"
abstract: >-
  AIF is a semantic document format and Rust toolchain for LLMs.
  Compiles typed documents to 12+ formats with the best structure-per-token
  ratio: full semantic types at 22% fewer tokens than Markdown.
  Skills in AIF LML format improve LLM compliance by 10 percentage points
  vs raw Markdown. Includes document cleaning/normalization for HTML, PDF,
  and Markdown; typed skill authoring with versioning and eval pipelines;
  and a codebase migration engine with LLM-powered verification and repair.
keywords:
  - llm
  - semantic-format
  - document-compiler
  - skill-authoring
  - token-efficiency
  - ai-native
